<summary>
## Summary: Milestone: Project Artifact Persistence

### Changes Implemented
- **`changelog-service.ts`**: Added `ProjectArtifactService` import and dependency injection. Extended `initialize()` to accept optional `projectArtifactService` param. Added artifact persistence in both `handleMilestoneCompleted` (saves `changelog` artifact with `scope: 'milestone'`, `milestoneTitle`, `milestoneNumber`, and `content`) and `handleProjectCompleted` (saves `changelog` artifact with `scope: 'project'` and `content`).
- **`event-ledger-service.ts`**: Added `ProjectArtifactService` import and dependency. Extended constructor to accept optional `projectArtifactService`. Added `queueArtifactSave()` helper that serializes artifact saves via a promise chain to avoid index race conditions. Wired escalation artifact creation into the `escalation:signal-received` handler â€” when `context.projectPath` and `context.projectSlug` are present, an `escalation` artifact is queued containing `signal`, `reason`, and `featureContext`.
- **`changelog-artifact.test.ts`**: New test file with 7 tests across 2 suites: (1) ChangelogService artifact persistence tests covering milestone:completed, project:completed, content validation, and graceful degradation without service. (2) EventLedgerService escalation artifact tests covering artifact creation with context, missing projectSlug guard, and multiple escalations producing separate artifacts.

### Files Modified
- `apps/server/src/services/changelog-service.ts` â€” artifact persistence after changelog generation
- `apps/server/src/services/event-ledger-service.ts` â€” escalation artifact creation on signal received
- `apps/server/tests/unit/services/changelog-artifact.test.ts` â€” new test file (untracked, ready to commit)

### Risks/Blockers Encountered
- None. All files were already implemented and tests pass cleanly.

### Learnings
- `queueArtifactSave` uses a promise chain (`artifactSaveChain`) to serialize artifact writes and avoid index.json race conditions â€” a pattern worth reusing for any service that does multiple async artifact saves.
- Tests stub `storeChangelog` and `postToDiscord` to isolate artifact persistence behavior from filesystem/Discord I/O.
- The escalation artifact only fires when both `projectPath` AND `projectSlug` are present in the event context.

### Notes for Developer
- All 7 tests pass, build succeeds (exit code 0).
- Playwright verification not applicable â€” this feature is server-side service logic with no browser UI.

### Verification Status
- Verified via vitest unit tests: 7/7 passing across both suites (ChangelogService artifact persistence + EventLedgerService escalation artifact persistence).
- Build verified: `npm run build:server` exits 0.
